<br>
Mages were never great nukers.  I'm not that concerned about not having or ever getting a Lure style nuke.  That's wizard stuff, and more power to em for it.<br>
<br>
Mages were about pets, and pets need to be looked at.<br>
<br>
Making summoned weapons with good procs is an obvious and easy solution, IMO.<br>
<br>
As you say, a pet weapon that procs a 100 point Lure could be ideal.  It makes our pets more powerful in melee, which has historically been the whole point of the magician class.<br>
<br>
It's easy to tweak.  If they screw up they can just change the weapon stats without worry -- since they're summoned weapons we don't keep them from day to day anyway.  If there's no obvious way to make the weapons &quot;pet only&quot;, you can avoid balance issues by simply making them have bad stats.<br>
<br>
To Jobaber, a weapon that's 1 damage and 50 delay but procs a 100pt DD is an awesome weapon.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Simply increasing the native damage ability of out pets across the board is another happy solution.<br>
<br>
Just Say No To Mod Rod III.<br>
